  "title": "Sales Engineer (Entry-Level/Fresh Graduates Welcome)",
  "description": "<p><em>An exciting opportunity for individuals with a background or strong interest in Business or Engineering to build a rewarding career in consultative, solution-based sales. You will receive full training to understand our products and applications and work closely with customers to provide tailored solutions that enhance their operations.</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Learn and apply product knowledge through structured training and on-the-job experience.</li>\n  <li>Conduct customer visits to understand technical needs and propose effective solutions.</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain strong relationships with clients across various industries.</li>\n  <li>Identify new business opportunities and contribute to overall sales growth.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and deliver presentations, product demonstrations, and sales reports as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Business, Engineering, or a related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Strong interest in <strong>technology, manufacturing, and sales.</strong></li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, presentation, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Self-motivated, goal-oriented, and eager to learn.</li>\n  <li>Possess a <strong>valid Class 3 driving licence</strong>, as the role involves client visits.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
